{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00245/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00245"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:02:45"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Women ascend a spiral staircase."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00245","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00245"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/8ebefc3b-eb99-42f0-be2d-ff1301d5be12","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:35:22.831Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The spotted underside of the staircase suggests that something isn’t quite right in the House of Woodcock. Underneath the veneer of respectability and perfection lies something else: dirtier, messier, darker.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:66.66788321167878,407.00364963503654,588.5255474452555,415.43430656934305"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/9172bc59-e669-43b8-a8ee-5700dde99075","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:35:37.716Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The stairs are winding, and while this characteristic lends grandiosity to the space, it also visualizes the twists and turns that the story will take as we discover Reynolds’ personality traits and deepest desires. The staircase features prominently throughout the film, often at times of juncture.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:798.4598540145985,347.616788321168,503.5182481751824,538.390510948905"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1/9af680f2-afcc-4060-b4dc-dddbcd5cf47c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:35:53.485Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Like <em>There Will Be </em>Blood and unlike <em>Punch-Drunk Love</em>, <em>Phantom Thread</em> is a film built on vertical shots and transitions. That is, much of the camerawork tilts, rather than pans (horizontally). In this case, such movement often suggests changes in power dynamics between characters. Here, along with the bright light and Jonny Greenwood’s swooning score, it evokes a sense of grandeur and wonder as viewers are made to look upward.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00245/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:811.992700729927,35.37591240875912,498.043795620438,275.95620437956217"}}}]}]}]}